From Subject Government and Technolgy Investment People who criticize big Government and its projects rarely seem to have a consistent view of the role of Government in science and Basically the Government has gotten into the role of supporting research which private industry finds too expensive or too long Historically this role for the Gov't was forced upon it because of socialism in other In order for industries to compete with government subsidized foreign competitors the Gov't has taken on the role of subisizing big ticket or long lead R As a Republican I abhor the necessity for our Government to involve itself in technology this I believe that market forces should drive technology and the world would be a better place for But the whole world would have to implement this concept simultaneously or some countries would have subsidized R D while others would So the must subsidize because everybody else This sounds a lot like the farm subsidies arguments behind our GATT negotiations doesn't it But this role of Government subsidies is antithetical to cost The general idea is to spend money on new technology and thereby maintain and promote our technological culture despite the forces in the business world like the dreaded quarterly earnings report which erode the ability of industry to invest in new And since our goal is to spend money it makes little sense to try to save Of course we could always spend our money more wisely but EVERYBODY disagrees about that the wisdom should It's interesting to note that some of our best tools for cost control available in industry today were derived from Government GANTT charts CP M and most of the modern scheduling software comes from DoD projects and their The construction industry has taken these tools to the core of their businesses every large construction project now uses these Ken Jenks NASA JSC Space Shuttle Program Office A scientist can discover a new star but he cannot make He would have to ask an engineer to do Gordon